description:
Kate has some things to say about boobs and recent buys and Doree takes her challah baking to the next level. Then, Fatima Iqbal-Zubair (Candidate for California State Assembly member) joins them to share her daily tea routine, what the hardest part of running for office has been, and what keeps her motivated to stay in the race. 


To leave a voicemail or text for a future episode, reach us at 781-591-0390. You can also email the podcast at forever35podcast@gmail.com.


Visit forever35podcast.com for links to everything we mention on the show.
